22/09/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Police announced on Monday (September 21st) the arrest of nine people allegedly connected to a human trafficking network. Eight illegal immigrants in poor health were found in a house in Nikea, near the port of Piraeus. The immigrants were from Bangladesh, Pakistan and Afghanistan. Police say they came from Turkey to the Evia region, where they were taken by truck to Nikea. In the house there, they were allegedly beaten repeatedly and blackmailed into paying 4,000 euros each for their release. (ANA-MPA, BTA - 21/09/09)
